snippet.textDisplay:
They'll probably lose a couple of games towards the end of the season if they're still in the CL and the PL is wrapped up, and they're playing against teams that still have something to play for. That's not to say this is not a phenomenal team that could go unbeaten, but everything can change when injuries start piling up and you're playing a team that need to win/draw or get relegated.


That said, the PL is all but done. The highest total points any other team can get is 92, if they win every remaining game, which means Liverpool could lose 6 games and still win the PL if they won all the other games. If they somehow managed to throw it away, it would be as shocking as when Leicester won the PL imo.
